<p>
<seg id=1> Although the security troops of Serbia and the Albanian separatists carried on the fighting for a couple of days, the international supervisors to Kosovo still entertain hopes on resuming a cease-fire. </seg>
<seg id=2> A spokesman of the supervisors addressed in Pristina on Monday that the situation in Kosovo Province, Yugoslavia was calm. </seg>
<seg id=3> At least 12 people were killed in the fighting last week. </seg>
<seg id=4> Polishman Gelmake, Chairman of European Security and Cooperation Organization criticized both sides on the violent conflict. </seg>
